<HEADLINE>
MEETING OF TAIWAN'S LODGING ASSOCIATIONS TO BE HELD JUNE 5
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, June 4 (CNA) 06/04/07  21:18:43 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Associations of lodginghouse owners will have a two-day meeting
in the Chiayi County mountain resort of Alisha n June 5-6 for
exchanges of views on futurecooperation, an official of the
county's Tourism Bureau said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, organized by the county's lodging association, is
aimed at promoting cooperation  in the lodging industry among
different areas of the country, the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, lodging house owners in Yilan,
Hualien, Taipei, Miaoli, Taichung, Yunlin and Chiayi counties
have been invited to attend the meeting. The Tourism Bureau, the
Alishan National Scenic Area Administration and the Chiayi County
Tourism Bureau will also have representatives present at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Wang San-hua, director-general of the organizing association,
said the lodging industry is an indicator of an area's tourism
development and that as the county's lodging industry is still
growing, the association hopes to hold more exchange activities
to boost the industry.
</P>
<P>
There will be keynote speeches on the development of Taiwan's
lodging industry and an introduction to Alishan's tea industry
during the meeting. Participants will also visit the county's
scenic spots, including a national park and a restored old street
to gain a better understanding of the county, the official added.
</P>
